# Project installation instructions

Docker is now the recommended way to run this project because it starts both the FastAPI app and PostgreSQL database together.

1. Install Docker Desktop (or Docker Engine) and Docker Compose.

2. Make sure Python 3.12 is available if you want to run the project locally outside Docker.

3. Create a `.env` file in the project root with:

   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:1353@postgres:5432/hackathon
   SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
   ALGORITHM=HS256
   ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=60

   The hostname `postgres` is the database service name defined in `docker-compose.yml`.

4. Build and start the containers:

   docker compose up --build

   This will start:
   - FastAPI API at http://127.0.0.1:8000
   - PostgreSQL database on port 5432

5. Run database migrations in a separate terminal:

   docker compose exec api alembic upgrade head

6. Open the API docs in your browser:

   http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

7. To stop the containers:

   docker compose down

8. To stop the containers and remove the database volume:

   docker compose down -v

Optional: if you want to run the app locally without Docker, create a virtual environment and install dependencies:

   python -m venv .venv
   .venv\Scripts\activate
   python -m pip install --upgrade pip
   pip install -r requirements.txt

   Then run:

   uvicorn app.main:app --reload
